Section 1: Data and Motivation

# Load the data
Delays <- read.csv("flight_data.csv")

Section 2: Data Cleaning and EDA

# Remove rows that occur Jan - Nov
Delays1 <- Delays[Delays$month == "12", ]
# Remove columns that are collected after the flight has taken off
Delays2 <- Delays1[-c(4,7,9,15)]
# Remove year, month, tail number 
Delays3 <- Delays2[-c(1,2,8,9,15,14,13)]
# Clean the data 
Delays4 <- na.omit(Delays3)
# Build box plots to explore departure delay and distance 
g1 <- ggplot(Delays4, aes(dep_delay)) + geom_boxplot(fill = "white", col = "blue") + labs(title ="Figure 2.1", x="Total Departure Delay (in minutes)")
g2 <- ggplot(Delays4, aes(distance)) + geom_boxplot(fill = "white", col = "blue") + labs(title ="Figure 2.2", x="Distance (in miles)")
gridExtra::grid.arrange(g1,g2, ncol = 2)

# Remove outliers from data 
Delays5 <- Delays4[Delays4$distance < 3000, ]
Delays6 <- Delays5[Delays5$distance > 500, ]
Delays7 <- Delays6[Delays6$dep_delay > -20, ]
Delays8 <- Delays7[Delays7$dep_delay < 20, ]

# Build box plots to explore departure delay and distance

Section 3: KNN

3.2: Method

# Make a 2 Variable Plot 
ggplot(Delays8, aes(x=day , y = distance, color=dep_delay)) + geom_point() + labs(title="Figure 3.1", x="Day of December", y="Distance Between Airports (in miles)")

# Train the KNN model 

# Create the folds 
papers <- rep(1:10, 2711)
set.seed(420)
foldsDelays <- sample(papers, 27110)

# Create the Storage Spaces
storageDelays <- data.frame("YHat"=rep(NA, 27110))
storageKNN <- data.frame("K"=rep(NA, 25), "RMSE"=rep(NA, 25))

# Run For Loop for k values 1-10 
for (k in 1:25) {
  # Store k 
  storageKNN[k,1] <- k
# Run For Loop for 10-Fold CV 
for( f in 1:10){
  set.seed(420)
# Find the Data in the Folds
InfoldDelays <- which(foldsDelays==f)
# Create Training and Test 
testDelays <- Delays4[InfoldDelays, ]
trainDelays <- Delays4[-InfoldDelays, ]
# Make Predictions
K_preds <- knn(trainDelays[,c(1,2,4,8)], testDelays[,c(1,2,4,8)], k = k,
cl = trainDelays$dep_delay )

# Store the prediction
storageDelays$YHat[InfoldDelays] <- as.numeric(as.character(K_preds))

# RMSE
storageKNN[k, 2] <- sqrt(mean((storageDelays$YHat - Delays4$dep_delay)^2))
}}
# Train the KNN model 

# Create the folds 
papers <- rep(1:10, 1627)
set.seed(420)
foldsDelays <- sample(papers, 16268)

# Create the Storage Spaces
storageDelays <- data.frame("YHat"=rep(NA, 16268))
storageKNN2 <- data.frame("K"=rep(NA, 25), "RMSE"=rep(NA, 25))

# Run For Loop for k values 1-10 
for (k in 1:25) {
  # Store k 
  storageKNN2[k,1] <- k
# Run For Loop for 10-Fold CV 
for( f in 1:10){
  set.seed(420)
# Find the Data in the Folds
InfoldDelays <- which(foldsDelays==f)
# Create Training and Test 
testDelays <- Delays8[InfoldDelays, ]
trainDelays <- Delays8[-InfoldDelays, ]
# Make Predictions
K_preds <- knn(trainDelays[,c(1,2,4,8)], testDelays[,c(1,2,4,8)], k = k,
cl = trainDelays$dep_delay )

# Store the prediction
storageDelays$YHat[InfoldDelays] <- as.numeric(as.character(K_preds))

# RMSE
storageKNN2[k, 2] <- sqrt(mean((storageDelays$YHat - Delays8$dep_delay)^2))
}}

Section 4: Elastic Net

4.2: Method

# Construct design matrix manually 
XD <- model.matrix(dep_delay ~., data = Delays8)
# Choose a sequence of values for alpha 
alphaseq <- seq(from = 0, to =1 , by =.01)

storage <- data.frame("Alpha" = rep(NA,length(alphaseq)), "Lambda" = rep(NA,length(alphaseq)), "RMSE" = rep(NA,length(alphaseq)))

a = 1 
# Run 10-fold CV
set.seed(420)
for( i in alphaseq ){
  cv.out.enet <- cv.glmnet(XD, Delays8$dep_delay, alpha = i,lambda = seq(from = 0, to = 100, by = .5))
  storage$Lambda[a] <- cv.out.enet$lambda.min
  storage$RMSE[a] <- sqrt((min(cv.out.enet$cvm)))
  storage$Alpha[a] <- i
  a = a + 1 
}
# Display table 
knitr::kable(storage, caption = "Table 4.1: RMSE of Each Elastic Net Model")

Section 5: Bagged Regression Forests

5.2: Method

# Build classification tree 
tree <- rpart(dep_delay ~ day + carrier, method = "anova", data = Delays4, cp=.008)

fancyRpartPlot(tree, sub = "Figure 5.1")

# Build classification forest WITH outliers 
set.seed(420)
forest <- randomForest(dep_delay ~ ., data = Delays4, mtry = 7, importance=TRUE, ntree=200, compete=FALSE)
# Build classification forest WITHOUT outliers 
set.seed(420)
forest1 <- randomForest(dep_delay ~ ., data = Delays8, mtry = 7, importance=TRUE, ntree=1000, compete=FALSE)
